    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Job Growth Cuts Crime</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jay Fishman letter says Mayor Edward Rendell of Philadelphia should know that the 'new' gun controls he is calling for were signed into law in 1994 and 1996</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report (front page, Dec. 24) that Mayor Edward G. Rendell of Philadelphia believes that pressure from municipal handgun litigation may lead to new gun controls, like ''a halt to the production of large clips for handguns and bullets that can pierce police armor.'' Both of these controls were enacted by Congress and signed into law in 1994 and 1986, respectively. Is Mayor Rendell really so woefully ignorant on the subject of gun control, for which he has made himself a spokesman?</p>
        <p>JAY  FISHMAN  Stamford, Conn., Dec. 24, 1998</p>
      </block>
